ce:section.ce:para:
Colloidal Au NPs prepared by the traditional reduction method were characterized to inspect the dispersion state. UV–Vis absorption spectrum in Fig. 1
                        A showed that there was an obvious absorption peak at 520 nm, which was the typical curve of monodispersed Au NPs with diameter around 20–25 nm according to calculation in previous report(Wang et al., 2021; 
                        Huang, et al., 2021). TEM and DLS results (Fig. 1B and inset) also proved the free dispersion state and narrow size distribution (24 nm) of obtained Au NPs. The negative charges endowed by citrate ligand on the surface made the synthesized Au NPs uniformly dispersed in their free state.
